:: \ confronting the bird {"position":"800,800","size":"100,100"}
(text-colour:cyan)[''Mouse'']<br>
You and the sausage return home and confront the bird about the whole situation. You tell him everything. The bird is appalled by the situation that he's put his partners in. In disgust with himself, he allows each person to return to their original roles. You all live happily ever after. <br>[[The end.->End]]


:: \ confrontingbird {"position":"1200,1000","size":"100,100"}
(text-colour:cyan)[''Mouse'']<br>
Almost home, you and the sausage you are holding up see a stack of smoke coming from where your house is. You both rush to see the house up in flames. The bird apparently does not know how to cook. With only you and the sausage remaining in this partnership you decide it's best you split up and go your separate ways to keep each other out of danger. <br>[[The end.->End]]


:: Beginning {"position":"1100,100","size":"100,100"}
<img src="https://mir-s3-cdn-cf.behance.net/project_modules/disp/f71d228672929.560c17ce0b5fe.png"></img>
<br>
Once upon a time, a mouse, a bird, and a sausage, entered into partnership and set up house together. For a long time all went well; they lived in great comfort, and prospered so far as to be able to add considerably to their stores. The birdâ€™s duty was to fly daily into the wood and bring in fuel; the mouse fetched the water, and the sausage saw to the cooking.<br>[[Bird]]<br>[[Mouse]]<br>[[Sausage]]


:: Bird {"position":"600,300","size":"100,100"}
(text-colour:cyan)[''Bird'']<br>
When people are too well off they always begin to long for something new. And so it came to pass, you, while out one day, met a fellow bird, to whom he boastfully expatiated on the excellence of his household arrangements. But the other bird sneered at you for being a poor simpleton, who did all the hard work, while your partners stayed at home and had a good time of it. <br>Was the Other Bird right?<br> [[Agree->agree]] <br>[[Disagree->disagree]]


:: Bird Investigate {"position":"300,600","size":"100,100"}
(text-colour:cyan)[''Bird'']<br>
You got a shiny rock! [[Nice!]]


:: Don'tInvestigate {"position":"1000,700","size":"100,100"}
(text-colour:cyan)[''Mouse'']<br>
After a time the sausage remained so long away, that you and the bird became uneasy, and the bird flew out to meet him. He had not flown far, however, when he came across a dog who, having met the sausage, had regarded him as food and so seized and swallowed him. Heartbroken you still try to [[make dinner]].


:: End {"position":"1000,1200","size":"100,100"}
