:: Face cat {"position":"400,700","size":"100,100"}
(text-colour:cyan)[''Bird'']<br>
You face the cat, get your water, and escape unharmed.  On returning to your house and meeting the mouse, you notice that the sausage hasn't returned yet.  Do you want to invesigate? <br> [[Yes]] <br>[[No]]


:: FirewoodSausage {"position":"1500,500","size":"100,100"}
(text-colour:cyan)[''Sausage'']<br>
You go out to gather firewood, and on your way you see a hungry dog.  It starts to run towards you, do you want to [[drop the firewood and run]], or [[hang on to your fuel]]?


:: Mouse {"position":"1100,300","size":"100,100"}
(text-colour:cyan)[''Mouse'']<br>
The mouse had made the fire and fetched in the water. Now she could retire into her little room and [[rest]] until it was time to set the table, or she could [[set it]] right away.


:: MouseDeny {"position":"1000,600","size":"100,100"}
(text-colour:cyan)[''Mouse'']<br>
You plead and plead and try to stand your ground against the bird. However, the bird is stronger and starts making threats. You are now forced to cook. <br>[[Darn.->MouseWait]]


:: MouseFirewood {"position":"1100,600","size":"100,100"}
(text-colour:cyan)[''Mouse'']<br>
On your way to the woods to collect firewood, you spot something shiny out of the corner of your eye! Do you want to go investigate?  <br>[[Yes->MouseInvestigate]] <br>[[No->MouseNoInv]]


:: MouseInvestigate {"position":"1100,700","size":"100,100"}
(text-colour:cyan)[''Mouse'']<br>
You got a shiny rock! [[Nice!->MouseNoInv]]


:: MouseNoInv {"position":"1200,800","size":"100,100"}
(text-colour:cyan)[''Mouse'']<br>
Now you go pick up your firewood like the good little mouse you are. You head back to the house, finding the bird relaxing while waiting to cook. The sausage has been out for a while now. It's getting concerning. Do you go [[look for him]] or [[wait it out]]?


:: MouseWait {"position":"900,600","size":"100,100"}
(text-colour:cyan)[''Mouse'']<br>
While sitting at the fire, alone with your thoughts and waiting for the supplies you hear a noise. <br>Do you go [[investigate]], or [[not->Don'tInvestigate]]?


:: NextMorning {"position":"1000,500","size":"100,100"}
(text-colour:cyan)[''Mouse'']<br>
The bird next morning refused to bring in the wood, telling the others that he had been their servant long enough, and had been a fool into the bargain, and that it was now time to make a change, and to try some other way of arranging the work. Do you want to [[gather firewood->MouseFirewood]], [[cook->MouseWait]] or [[deny->MouseDeny]] the job change completely?


:: Nice! {"position":"400,600","size":"100,100"}
(text-colour:cyan)[''Bird'']<br>
You continue to the creek, and you see a cat near the water!  Do you want to proceed, knowing the cat may attack? <br>[[Face cat]] <br>[[Return home->return home]]


:: No {"position":"400,800","size":"100,100"}
(text-colour:cyan)[''Bird'']<br>
The sausage never returns, lost to the world.  With no wood, you cannot make dinner tonight. The mouse blames you for changing all of their jobs, and sets out on her own.  Without dinner, you starve to death. <br>[[The end.->End]]


:: Sausage {"position":"1700,300","size":"100,100"}
(text-colour:cyan)[''Sausage'']<br>
You had only to watch the pot to see that the food was properly cooked. When it was near dinner-time, you could just throw yourself into the broth, and rolled in and out among the vegetables three or four times, and there they were, buttered, and salted, and ready to be served.<br>[[Just watch->watch the pot]] or [[Jump in->throw yourself]]


:: Yes {"position":"300,800","size":"100,100"}
(text-colour:cyan)[''Bird'']<br>
You find a dog that claims he has eaten the sausage while the sausage was getting wood.  You gather the wood left behind and carry it back to the house.  When the mouse goes to cook the meal, she realizes that she cannot cook, and burns the house down, and you both die.  <br>[[The end.->End]]


:: agree {"position":"500,400","size":"100,100"}
(text-colour:cyan)[''Bird'']<br>
Influenced by those remarks, the next morning you refused to bring in the wood, telling the others that you had been their servant long enough, and had been a fool into the bargain, and that it was now time to make a change, and to try some other way of arranging the work.  The others pleaded and pleaded, but you did not relent.  Do you want to [[get water]] or [[cook]]?


:: cook {"position":"500,500","size":"100,100"}
(text-colour:cyan)[''Bird'']<br>
When the others return with their supplies, you start cooking, but you do not know how.  You burn down the house, and when going to fetch water to put it out, you drown in the well. <br>[[The end.->End]]


:: disagree {"position":"600,400","size":"100,100"}
(text-colour:cyan)[''Bird'']<br>
Then, when you came home and had laid aside your burden, you all sat down to table, and when you all had finished your meals, you all could sleep your fill till the following morning: and that was really a very delightful life. <br>[[The end.->End]]


:: drop the firewood and run {"position":"1400,600","size":"100,100"}
(text-colour:cyan)[''Sausage'']<br>
You escape the dog, but have to drop the firewood in the process! With your wood being guarded by a dog, you return back to the house empty handed, finding the bird and the mouse waiting for you. Do you want to [[explain what happened]] or [[not explain->return back to the house fire]]?


:: explain what happened {"position":"1400,800","size":"100,100"}
(text-colour:cyan)[''Sausage'']<br>
The mouse sides with you, and the bird feels remorse.  He apologizes and you go back to your original jobs the next day.  <br>[[The end.->End]]


:: full bucket {"position":"1700,600","size":"100,100"}
(text-colour:cyan)[''Sausage'']<br>
You attempt to go back for a full bucket, but you cannot carry the weight back to the surface.  It drags you down and you drown at the bottom of the creek.  <br>[[The end.->End]]


:: get water {"position":"400,500","size":"100,100"}
(text-colour:cyan)[''Bird'']<br>
On your way to collect water, you spot something shiny out of the corner of your eye!  Do you want to go investigate?  <br>[[Yes->Bird Investigate]] <br>[[No->Nice!]]


:: go back {"position":"1600,600","size":"100,100"}
(text-colour:cyan)[''Sausage'']<br>
You decide it is too dangerous for you to try to get a full bucket, as you don't even have hands, for you are a sausage. You [[return back to the house]] with a half full bucket. 


:: hang on to your fuel {"position":"1500,600","size":"100,100"}
(text-colour:cyan)[''Sausage'']<br>
The firewood is heavy, and you cannot outrun the dog while carrying it!  The dog catches up to you and swallows you whole. <br>[[The end.->End]]


:: investigate {"position":"800,700","size":"100,100"}
(text-colour:cyan)[''Mouse'']<br>
The noise was a barking dog! The sausage is running away from the rabid mutt in a panic. Ahh! You race to intervene pulling the sausage into hiding around a rock. You realize that this job was too [[dangerous for the sausage -> confronting the bird]].


:: look for him {"position":"1200,900","size":"100,100"}
(text-colour:cyan)[''Mouse'']<br>
After roaming for a while you see the sausage running away from a rabid mutt in a panic. Ahh! You race to intervene pulling the sausage into hiding behind a rock. You realize that this job was too [[dangerous for the sausage -> confrontingbird]].


:: make dinner {"position":"1000,800","size":"100,100"}
(text-colour:cyan)[''Mouse'']<br>
While crying and still heartbroken you did not pay attention to the growing flames that swallowed you to a fiery death. <br>[[The end.->End]]


:: rest {"position":"1000,400","size":"100,100"}
(text-colour:cyan)[''Mouse'']<br>
You decide to take a nap before you set the table. After waking up to a wonderful little sleep, you are energetic and set the table with ease. <br>[[Yay!->NextMorning]]


:: return back to the house {"position":"1600,800","size":"100,100"}
(text-colour:cyan)[''Sausage'']<br>
You apologize for the half full bucket, but the bird doesn't want to hear it.  He kicks you out, so you try to go back to your sausage family. While traveling to your true sausage home, a pack of wild humans finds you out in the sun, cooked to perfection. Turns out they were hungry. You have been eaten. <br>[[The end.->End]]


:: return back to the house fire {"position":"1500,800","size":"100,100"}
(text-colour:cyan)[''Sausage'']<br>
